{
  "name": "07 \u2014 At-Risk Customer Detection",
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "SETUP\n\n1. This workflow imports inactive. Walk every node, attach your own credentials (none are included \u2014 n8n never exports secrets), then run a manual execution with test data before activating.\n\n2. Placeholder values (channel names, table IDs, URLs, prompts) need replacing with yours \u2014 see the README in Appendix B.\n\n3. AI / vector nodes may need a typeVersion nudge on import depending on your installed n8n version; if a node shows an error on import, delete and re-add it from the node panel.\n\nReference: Appendix B, Learn Automation Working.",
        "height": 420,
        "width": 380,
        "color": 4
      },
      "id": "aba61bb3-4c7f-4d09-9ae3-7518f8947aa7",
      "name": "Setup notes",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -460,
        -40
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "days",
              "triggerAtHour": 7
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "id": "f7051384-0891-4a77-8dbf-6ebbe19bf396",
      "name": "Schedule (daily 7AM)",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.scheduleTrigger",
      "typeVersion": 1.2,
      "position": [
        0,
        0
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "operation": "executeQuery",
        "query": "SELECT account_id, current_week, previous_week FROM usage WHERE previous_week > 0 AND current_week::float/previous_week < 0.6"
      },
      "id": "ba252b70-402b-4edf-ad6d-380af3c62742",
      "name": "Postgres: usage drops",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.postgres",
      "typeVersion": 2.5,
